# .oss-gitignore
#
# Machine-readable exclude list for pushes to the public open source repository:
#   https://github.com/IBM/substrait-compliance
#
# This file is NOT a standard .gitignore — it does not affect the private
# main repository at github.ibm.com/rsinha/substrait-compliance.
#
# Usage when pushing to the public remote:
#   git push public main
#   (files listed here are tracked in the private repo but absent from
#    the public repo because they were removed via `git rm --cached` and
#    are listed here so the intent is explicit and auditable)
#
# To add a new exclusion:
#   1. Add the path below with a comment explaining why.
#   2. Run: git rm --cached -r <path>
#   3. Update OSS_EXCLUDE.md with the same entry.
#   4. Commit both files together.
#
# Last updated: July 11, 2026

